<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 05 at 2:27AM EST  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...Lake Effect Snow Through The Early Morning...
Lake effect snow will continue through the early morning hours.
The stronger bands will reduce visibilities below one half mile
with snowfall rates briefly up to an inch per hour at times.
Several inches of additional accumulation are possible in some
spots through the morning hours. Anyone travelling through the
early morning is urged to slow down, be prepared for rapid changes
in conditions, and leave plenty of stopping distance. The snow
will gradually taper off after sunrise.</description>
